caption: Lots of great vegan choices in a friendly played back atmosphere. Very tasty soups and stir frys to choose from.
Great restaurant in downtown Frederick with options for everyone - meat, seafood, vegan, and organic. They even had a vegan coffee cake as one dessert option! Everyone enjoyed their meals.
Great little place that perfectly balances organic, vegan, and regular food options for everyone.   Great service as well!
This is my most fav restaurant.. i have been going here since the past 9 years..
Food is good, staff are very accommodating but they need more spacious place.

We were in town, and looking for somewhere local and quaint. Orchard Restaurant fit the bill. Friendly service, terrific food, and plenty of variety so there were something for everyone. Definitely recommend.
Great food. Well priced.

We each had a stir fry bowl and they were both AMAZING. You chose your protein (or not if you want just veggies) and it is loaded with veggies. Great atmosphere and they had a vegan coffee cake that was amazing.
Delightful fusion cuisine and terrific service.
My FIRST time trying the Thai Lime Peanut Stir Fry Bowl with Crunchy Sesame Tofu and Soba noodles. OMG! THE BEST!
Excellent, healthy food. We have never been disappointed.
Never disappointed eating here

The Orchard was excellent, as usual.  Everything on the menu looks delicious, but I go there for creole stir fry with chicken and shrimp for lunch or jambalaya for dinner.  Also often have tomato bisque or  gazpacho that are worth the trip alone.  And they have excellent black iced tea, with herbal as an option.
Fresh great tasting food and always friendly service
Great food, excellent service, beautiful facility

The orchard has the best food with incredible service every time we eat there the food is delicious and hot and tasty. Being vegetarian this is a great place to get a good vegetarian meal with my non-vegetarian friends.

Good food and they have several vegetarian options! Tomato bisque was amazing, zucchini parm was nice and crisp, but a bit too much cheese and butter in the pasta. The other pastas my family ordered were great, but I was told the pad thai was a bit of a let down, a bit bland and lacking the authentic flavor. Overall a good dining experience

hands down one of the best restaurants in Frederick! all the wonderful staff really care about the food they serve and I can tell that a lot of love goes into the outstanding food. the orchard veggie sandwich was to die for and the Primavera stir fry was absolutely amazing! everything was so delicious that there were no leftovers! I'll definitely be back to try the many other things on the menu.

I've been going here regularly for 10 years and I am obsessed with this place, the staff and the quality of the food. I always get the veggie salad but everything I've tried has been delish. My friends prefer the stir-fry or the salmon salad.  I love the cozy interior and the bustling patio. They always have great drink specials and the salad is HUGE and fresh every single time. Love the Orchard!!
Food was very good, service was amazing, and prices were about average for downtown Frederick.
Ordered the chef salad, lemonade, and iced herbal tea for carry out. Food was delicious, refreshing, and filling. Felt genuinely cared for by the staff.
Delicious and good service.
best food around
We had a wonderful experience at this restaurant. We enjoyed the superb vibes and the meals. The staff were super friendly. I am glad we ultimately decided to visit here.
Amazing food and always great service! Truly wonderful place to dine.
Outstanding in every way. Top notch service, cozy atmosphere, delicious food. I couldn't recommend a place more. Will definitely be back soon!
Great organic and local food, very nice and accomodating staff, and nice atmosphere
Food is always good and plentiful. Service is prompt and courteous. Excellent salads. Great coconut cream pie!

We were greeted and seated promptly. The service was good, our waiter was polite and answered all of our questions and checked on us accordingly. The food was hot and fresh with good portions and flavor. We had the spinach and asparagus soup I would add cheese 🙂 The vegetarian bbq soup, grilled chicken salad and the salmon entree special. We also had the daily mimosa which was an apple cider mimosa - it needed a little orange (which was included) to bring out the flavor. The menu selection is not large but I think they have enough options that suites the business and clientele.

Food and service are excellent.  Always. Quieter than many of the downtown "noise" establishments,  which is perfect. Always find a new surprise on the menu when we go. I cant think of a negative...ohhh wait....it was raining when we ate there last.😎
Service with a smile! Clean decor, menus weren't too busy. The food came out promptly and without any issues.  Tasty , tasty tasty is all I can say. Thanks Orchard, we'll be back!!

Actually I made a mistake. It should be 5 stars. The food is always fresh. I like the Chef's creations and spices. The service had always been excellent. I have been frequenting this restaurant for over 10 years and have never been disappointed.

We loved it! We were seated immediately, ordered lemonade and tea. The lemonade was perfect!! The portion of grilled salmon was very generous and done to perfection. Also got 2 shrimp & 2 sea scallops on a skewer over peanut noodles....DELICIOUS!! He got the chicken ranchero and loved it. Nice cozy atmosphere and the staff was wonderful! Prices on the online menu, however need to be updated.

Overall the restaurant is good. It is a nice restaurant that you can leave full but also feel like you had something healthy. Most food is international fusion. I would say any of the dishes are regionally authentic but I also don't think they are meant to be. They are more inspired by different regions.
Great food. Can't wait to go back.
I love all the food here!  Very fresh and delicious.  Cobb salad with tomato tamari dressing is my fav
Food is good, but the price is way too high and the venue could use some upgrades.
Better than expected, quality of food is incredible. Restaurant looks smaller from the outside.
Great fresh food and great service
Come for the food and the ambience. Staff is amazing and accommodating. I loved the fresh flavors and appeal of the foods served here. Definitely a stop to make when you're in downtown Frederick.
Many veg & vegan options. Really enjoyed our meal. Great location too.
Excellent food, service exceptional
Very unique and the food was amazing! Great wait staff as well!
Decent food. Small and cozy setting.
The food is always fresh and delicious!!  Never disappoints!  Highly recommend!!

This place myself and wife came to by sheer accident and it was an extraordinary place to eat. The service the food totally worth 5 stars and has excellent pricing. The staff is very knowledgeable of beers and food combinations. Thw salmon special with the tomato bisque was definitely 5 stars. If you're ever in the fredrick area stop by this place you will not be disappointed.
Excellent menu for allergies (gluten free and vegan options). Waiter was friendly, food was delicious and environment was cozy.
Nice atmosphere, quick and friendly service The food was great.  Best of all they offer gluten free options!

Good food, but the menu is very limited. They have about 3 wines, 4 beers and only have their own root beer, ginger beer and then water. The food is pretty good and you get a decent portion. I have only been here once and while it was ok, our server was not that good. We asked for a beer refill before our food was brought out to the table. She seemed happy to do for us and walked off. She was gone for about 20 minutes and brought us our food, but not the refills. A friend in our party said “thank you. And the beers?” Our waitress pursed her lips and looked irritated and said “and the beers” and walked off to, we assumed, get out drinks. We watched as she walked about to other tables, placed orders, went to the bar, got her phone out, talked to another server, answered the phone, sat another group of people, went back to talking to the other waiter, checked on another table and then FINALLY poured our beers and brought them to us. I will just say, they did have people in the place, but it was not crazy busy…. Anyway, when we were close to finishing our meals, we asked for the check, which was brought out to us. However, when our waitress collected the payment, the same thing happened. She placed the black checkbook on the counter that STILL contained our credit card, and proceeded to help other people and check on other tables. Our check and payment was left sitting for about 15 minutes. A friend in the party finally got up and went to the bar and asked for the bill to be paid because we had to leave for a show at the Weinberg Center that started fairly soon. The food was good, but I do not think it was enough to entice me in going back and possibly experiencing the same service.
Fast service and great food!

Usually when I see a bunch of different worlds of food on one menu, I think "there's no way they can do all of this right." The Orchard proves me wrong every time. It's a place you can bring people with vastly different palates and impress all of them. They also have gf and df options which I really appreciate. I personally love their vast selection of different stir fries, I can't even name a favorite, they've all been so good. I most recently had the Polynesian stir fry with grilled salmon and it was SO good!! Good portions, too, I always leave satisfied.  Oh yeah, and if you're just on a walk in downtown frederick, pop in for an apple cider to go. It's next level delicious, perfect thing to chase away the cold.
Great as usual!
Food was very good; thought the prices to a little high, but still willing to support local vendors
Great flavors
Most consistantly delicious place downtown.
Had appetizer and soup, service and food was excellent. No frozen products here made from scratch and has vegan and gluten free options .
Was seated very quickly. Staff was attentive. Appetizer, soup and entrée melded into a wonderful meal experience. Will definitely return!
I got a spicy chicken salad. It was good but not amazing. I did try my friend's tofu dish and it was really, really good. Prices are reasonable. Our service was great.

I was drawn by the local sourcing and plethora of vegetarian options while not being a vegetarian restaurant (it makes it easier to convince friends and family who are turned off by the idea of going to veggie places to go). The fun colours and variety of art and music give the Orchard a fun, eclectic vibe. I also found a stir fry bowl to be more than enough as a main course (I brought home leftovers!) when ordering an appetizing, and would probably have had almost half of something from the entree category left if I had an appetizer before. The Orchard Restaurant is definitely on my list of places to return to. Edit to add: I do want to mention that you shouldn't go in expecting authentic cuisine from any of the cultures represented on the menu; I would call the dishes more inspired by those cultures and their flavours.
Always great food!
They were closed for a week for summer vacation!!

We always enjoy dining at the Orchard.  It's a bit smaller and generally quieter and more relaxing than a number of the other restaurants in downtown Frederick.  It has a nice variety of delicious items: dinner/sandwiches/soups on the menu and is a great place for a mixed group of vegetarians and carnivores to patronize.
Simple and small place,but very nice staff food. I recommend! It's in downtown Frederick. But no worries on parking.

Not all of the menu speaks to me, but after 4 visits I finally had an excellent meal of Chicken Parmesan, a delicious Sangria, and blueberry cobbler.  All the food tastes and looks fresh, good service, and nice people.  For those who like Mediterranean and Polynesian food, they have a vast selection of stir fries and noodle dishes as well.
Amazing food and friendly staff! Great vegan, vegetarian and gluten free options.  Absolutely delicious!
Very good and high end service to go with the food.
Really great find in Fredericksburg. Unexpected,, slightly eclectic, creative, and super tasty.

Great service, great atmosphere and the food was good. They aren't joking when they say spicy though! I had the spicy chicken salad and it was putting my mouth on fire! Homemade bread with the salad was nice and the garlic dressing is everything I wanted it to be.
Love the great variety of choices, great food, reasonable prices
Had another great meal here.  Great service, too!

The food was pretty good. Our wait was really short and the staff was very polite. I'd recommend if you are looking for something more vegetarian/health friendly. They had ATTABOY on tap so I was pretty happy with the alcohol selection.
Good Vegan Options. Great service.
Good veggie fair.
No booze!!

My wife chose this place for lunch, and really liked her food I think. Mine was also good but the majority of the menu just wasn't appealing to me. They had some really unique dishes though, if you're a foodie you'd probably dig it.
Very tasty, laid back
Very friendly staff, good food at reasonable prices. It's in the middle of downtown frederick, so you'll need to bring some quarters to feed the parking meters
Variety for any taste  Been a customer ever since moving to area (18+ years)
Excellent food, friendly staff, and great prices. Highly recommend - the outdoor seating is also pleasant! I got the Polynesian Stir Fry, and it was delicious.
Delicious healthy food

Food was good but unfortunately the restaurant overcharged us for our food. It probably was an error. When we called the girl who helped us on the phone, Rebecca, did not know what she was doing. Instead of refunding she again charged us for $20.14 . We live in Potomac and they wanted us to come back to get a refund . Instead they should be courteous to atleast give us half off on the bill for all the inconvenience. Mistake is not yet resolved .Our waiter by the way was Jerome.

I was looking forward to trying this restaurant. The waiter did fine, and he provided quick service. We weren't offered or served bread like all the other diners, though. One beer on tap was oddly warm, so I just went with another. If chicken on a salad will be fried, it should be specified. If I order a salad, hoping for a healthy dish, fried chicken is a huge disappointment. Plus, the rest of the salad consisted of a lot of lettuce and quite small portions of the other vegetables. Disappointed...
My waitress was Ashley, and she was just fantastic!
Good food, friendly staff. Only downside is that it's in downtown Frederick. No trouble parking though.

Great food and gluten free options for gluten intolerant or any celiac disease folks. Service is away greatest, staff island friendly and accommodating. Usually busy so get on the wait list and walk around for a bit.
Lots of Vegetarian and Vegan Options. Food was delicious. Friendly staff.
Fresh and healthy. Always enjoy the food and service.
This is a clean, neat place with low music.  Excellent service and great food.  My taste buds thank you....
Excellent service, wonderful atmosphere. The food is phenomenal too, farm to table so its always fresh and bursting with flavor. Excellent variety of dishes too.
Fantastic  ... never been disappointed  !

Ever had a place that you walk by over and over and don't quite think about it? No longer for me at The Orchard. Variety sometimes is the spice of life as this menu proves, and with above expected results.
Great food and friendly staff
I've visited here on several occasions for lunch.  Their food is delicious and their staff is very good.  You cannot get a better vegetarian meal selection in Frederick.
Our favorite downtown restaurant!  For years!
My favorite restaurant. Healthy stir fries without the cleanup from cooking at home.
Great food at a good price with awesome veggies. The atmosphere was very welcoming with friendly staff. Looking forward to going again.
The best food, service, and atmosphere!
Very tasty stir fry that can cater to all tastes and preferences. The herbal tea was surpssurpris good. Fast service, and very affordable.

We love the Orchard Restaurant - eat there often. But if it was the gov  instead of Google that asked u out of blue how a restaurant was, wouldn't that creep u out?  So how is that different from a corporation doing it.
Chicken parmesan is to die for
Amazing food and atmosphere. One of my girlfriends favorite restaurants. We stop by frequently when we visit her parents! Highly recommend.
Always excellent...I just may bathe in their Tomato Tamari dressing. Cobb salad with fresh cooked salmon is my favorite.
All three of us in my party got food poisoning. Unfortunately this is a deal breaker for me. I won’t be back.
Great food and nice waitress!
One of the best places to eat in the city, and great prices. Service is always great, and food comes out fast

I don't go here often enough, it's really good.  The flavor profiles are interesting and varied.  Southern cajun, asian teriyaki, whatever you're in the mood for they probably have it. It's a great place for families or parties of varied tastes. There are many vegitarian or vegan choices;  many menu items start out vegitarian and your can add a protein of your choice. The kids menu is perfect, simple but good entree items with fruit and a salad. The atmosphere is cozy and much quieter than most other downtown restaurants.  Add in a good selection of beer, wine, and drink specials and you've got a fantastic night out.
Enjoy food and atmospheric
Great food and they are open 24/7. Food is really cheap.
Great variety of healthy,  fresh selections.  Pleasant atmosphere.  Everyone enjoyed their meal...6 adults and 2 children.
The food was absolutely delicious and the service was phenomenal! We left full and happy. I highly recommend it!
Fast friendly service and great food.
Friendly staff, comfortable atmosphere and great food!
Good service. Fresh food.
Charming, friendly, diverse menu in downtown Frederick.  Unusual fair, great staff, short wait for a table.  Will go here again for sure.
Flavorful, unique dishes with exotic, natural ingredients. Wait staff in also not the norn.
Exceptional service and food.  Always enjoy our meal and are regular guests.
Amazing food and the outside seating is a great summer spot to enjoy a fun evening out.

Better eat here before it becomes impossible to get a table.  Great selection of fresh healty food that is delicious.  May be only place in Frederick where Vegans and special diet needs can have selection.
Excellent experience.  Staff was great, food was amazing, and price was just right.  Will definitely be back.
A wonderful little restaurant that's one of my favorite places to go in Frederick.

Our food was great, but we were disappointed our server didn’t inform us that we were charged auto-gratuity on a party of four adults and two children under the age of three. I’m not opposed to auto-grat, but the server should inform you of such practices when they hand you the check. That said, the meal was excellent and the service other than not communicating auto-grat was great.

My favorite healthy meal restaurant in the city.  The food is extremely good and everyone that has helped me has been very kind.  They've always helped me at the door, made sure my ESA dog had water, and made extra certain that our food had nothing in it that I couldn't eat.  It's nice and quiet inside and the decorations encourage you to talk with people instead of staring at screens.  You can't beat chilling at the tables in front and watching the sights of downtown; can't beat their location.  Thanks guys!
Always DELICIOUS food, excellent customer service.

I have heard so many good things about this restaurant and we were really excited to finally try it. We went for he first time on pride day this past weekend so I understand that it was a little busy. The Japanese stir fry was very bland and so was the fried zucchini. My husband didn’t like his stir fry either. It’s like nothing had flavor and It was mostly veggies too. However, I’m mostly writing my first review ever because a staff member by the name of Jeff tried to take a toy away from my son. He should have asked one of us to take care of it. (Which we did try to but kids will be kids). Anyway, It freaked us out that a total stranger did that because he wasn’t even our waiter. Our waitress by the way, was very sweet though. WILL NOT BE COMING BACK!

Great place.   We were in town for an event and eat here two nights.  Coconut Curry Tofu dish is outstanding.   It's a must try place if you're in the area.   Wish is was not 4 hours away from where we live, or this would be a few nights a week place.    thanks for the great time and food!
I love this place! The food is incredibly delicious and fresh. I loved their house garlic dressing and the salmon salad.
Eclectic Asian/American inspired menu with a "healthier" vibe. Great staff, great beer, great location. Try the stir-fries.
Love the Orchard. Wonderful menu, wait staff and ambiance!
Amazing as always!
Great options for fresh organic food. Yummy. Fresh pita made on site. We elected multiple plates, everything had great taste and service.  Will go there alot.
Every flavor you could appreciate. Could eat here in any food mood! Service was splendid as well.

Great food with exceptional service!  There was hardly any wait time and the prices were definitely worth it. The atmosphere was very calm and cozy.  The food was fresh and light, but still very filling. Highly recommended.
Very fresh and healthy taste wise. The spicy tenders are a must try! But be careful, very spicy.
Food and service are consistently good in a comfortable environment and great location.
Fantastic food and service
One of my favorite places in Frederick. Food is fresh and tasty. Lots of options for vegetarians!
Delicious! So many gf choices. Amazing fruit and cheese plate.

Best Hummus in all of Frederick. Exceptionally friendly staff who are very knowledgeable with their menu and very attentive. Very cozy atmosphere with a patio out front. Great to come for lunch and very speedy take out. One of my favorite restaurants in Frederick.

Good service, great prices, tasty food.  You will enjoy your meal if you aren't expecting authentic, copycat stirfrys from your favorite ethnic restaurant. Or, just don't get the stirfry. Quality is very high, nice fresh veggies.

I love this place! If you have dietary restrictions or just care to eat a delicious and nourishing meal, you must try this restaurant. For the first time since being gluten and dairy free, I had many options from which to choose, including a "legal" dessert!

This place serves some of the most delish food in town. FYI, no red meat on the menu and I can't say I've ever seen any on the specials. That's not their thing. But they do amazing things with chicken, fish, tofu and veggies. Also, huge plus, rotating local craft beers on tap. They have a selection of local wine. No liquour. Wouldn't have a party there. But I can't think of any dinner occasion it wouldn't be a great choice for.
The Polynesian stir fry was OK. Can only imagine what it would taste like with pinnapple as there wasn't  any!
Delicious food and so many healthy options, even for vegans! Great beer/wine selection too!
Some of the best food to cross your lips. Is a bit on the pricey side, however, you get what you pay for! Highly recommend the jambalaya!
Great food, really enjoyed it. Service was great too

The orchard is hands down my favorite spot to eat in downtown Frederick. As a vegan, they're menu is plentiful with options for my dietary requirements. Don't ask where the protein comes from! Orchard good options always come with a delicious tofu cooked however you like it: savory crunch, or soft and salty!

The Japanese stir fry option on the menu is pretty good. I get it with tofu, because I don't eat meat. The best part about it is the large portion, so you can take some home. It's just as good reheated in the microwave two days later.
Always an enjoyable experience and tasty meal!

Charming little place in downtown Frederick MD with superb food, relaxed ambience and excellent staff. Staff is very knowledgeable and attentive without crossing the line to annoying. Heartily recommend the scallops as a starter.
Enjoyed a delicious meal, in very friendly and clean environment.  Excellent choice of you have a mix diet party (vegetarian, vegan, etc).
Fresh fresh fresh! Tomato tamari is amazing! Pear dessert is decadent! I love this place!
Good variety of vegetarian dishes.
Lunch was delicious! Best coconut pie ever!!
It has tasty vegan selections.

Food is tasty and fresh, with friendly service.
Soup was great, stir fry was good and sandwiches were meh. Crowded, trendy, good craft beer but pricey. Good overall, but no rush to return for me.
Loved this place. Food was great, cosy atmosphere, good service.
Delicious food and wonderful atmosphere. Vegan and vegetarian friendly- has enough options for each person's diet

Excellent food & service!!

Our experience was horrible.   My wife’s stir-fry bowl came with a dark hair on the plate, seen only seen after she had finished it.   We have light hair.  The waitress said to my wife, “Next time, send it back before you eat it.”      My tuna melt was cold, sent it back, returned cold again.   I RARELY leave less than a stellar review (5 star review, laudatory write-up of experience yesterday at Moonshadow in McHenry MD)  of any dining experience but this one was just shocking.   The worst part was the waitress treating us like scam artists.  We are retired professionals and extremely easy to please.
Always fresh and delicious
We ordered sandwiches, around 10 each.  Good tasting and fresh,  but the dish was screaming for something like baked chips or sweet potato fries! ! The sandwich felt very lonely.
Delicious place for a light lunch while driving through Frederick.
Delicious food!  Always hot! Awesome wait staff!  My favorite restaurant ever!
Very fresh food, excellent service.  Cool downtown Frederick vibe.

Very tasty food. My wife has lots of food allergies in addition to have Celiac. The server was patient and knew the menu well enough to make several wonderful suggestions. The atmosphere is nice but casual and quaint charm. Prices are good too.
Great food, great prices,  great service.  It has always been my favorite restaurant in Frederick.
Delicious!! Great service!
Great fresh food and lots of options. The Orchard is a must for anyone on a specific diet such as a vegetarian, vegan or gluten free. Love this place!

So delicious! Service was quick and our waitress was very nice. The food was so fresh and yummy. I ordered the southwest chicken sandwich and was so pleased. The bread was the best part, it tasted like it was made fresh just for my sandwich! I had such a hard time deciding what to order, everything on the menu looked so delicious.
We have been going here for 20+ years.  Delicious and healthy food with lots of options. Consistent wait staff who are kind, patient and skilled.
The service is always excellent and all of the food is so delicious. There are a lot of yummy vegan and vegetarian options. My whole family enjoys. The decor is nice as well.
Fresh food delightfully presented and delicious... Every time.
Very nice place with good food.
Food and service are consistently wonderful!
Interesting and healthy food menu. Atmosphere is cool.
The food was hot and seemed fresh. There are a lot of options other than vegetarian and vegan. Good beer selection too
Excellent food. Excellent service. Everything is fresh.
Great restaurant with incredible menu an local produce
Totally delicious every time.   The tomato tamari dressing is amazing.
This place rocks!
Finally!!! They updated their decor! Always the tastiest, healthy and best food in Frederick!
Nice place with good vegetarian options!
Unique flavors and awesome service by K
World's best gazpacho.  Reasonable prices, fresh food, healthy options, great staff, what's not to like?!?
Excellent selection of food to satisfy all palates and it's fairly healthy depending on what you get.
Really good food & service. Tomato soup is really good. Carrot cake, lemon squares are fantastic. Cheesecake is uh-mazing!
I've been here five or six times and have had a good experience every time. The food is great, prices are decent, service is good. Highly recommended.
Nice relaxing atmosphere and great food. They have lots of fresh, healthy and vegetarian options.
Unique restaurant with unique menu in unique downtown Frederick
The stir fries are fine, but the salads are great!
This restaurant is awesome! Delicious food, lots of vegetarian options, decent prices and fantastic service. Would definitely eat here again!
Simply great food and service. We have eaten here many times and have never had a bad meal. Always great!!
Great service by friendly people. Decent food. Amazon home made dressings.
Best hummus & pita around!! Great food and great service; accompanied with wonderul ambiance.

Great food and a fun atmosphere. I fell in love with one of their hot sauces and our waitress went above and beyond to write down the recipe from the chef. Just overall a great experience in an awesome town.
Great spot for vegetarian dishes but also has chicken and fish for everyone else. Good soups too.
Plates not too filling very delightful very clean atmosphere and pleasant people walk out of there full but not uncomfortable

As a vegan, it can be really difficult finding options when eating out other than a side salad or hummus with pita bread (even this is somewhat rare). So finding a restaurant that serves multiple vegan options for me to choose from, and which are labeled as such, is a dream come true! Then when the food is delicious, the wine mellow, and the service attentive and friendly without hovering, I am delighted!  We started with a bottle of Gouguenheim Malbec (which was excellent) and we each had a side salad composed of romaine, shaved carrots, shredded purple cabbage, red onion slices and alfalfa sprouts. I ordered the only vegan dressing: sesame vinaigrette which was delicious. My husband had the tomato tamari, also delicious.  For our meal we each ordered a stir fry: my husband safely ordered the Szechuan with tofu which was good, but my meal stood out: a Creole stirfry, veggies only. It tasted just like jambalaya and has inspired me to try making this dish at home! Both stir fries were over organic brown rice which was cooked perfectly: not too crunchy, not too sticky.  I am really looking forward to returning...I almost ordered the Mediterranean stir fry, or I may order a vegan entree (imagine that!) I can't wait!
Seafood Satay is one of the best meals I have ever had. By far my favorite place to eat downtown, the service is always great and the food never disappoints. Fairly priced as well.
Really good food and a quirky atmosphere. I've been several times over the years and has always been a good experience.
Very nice place to enjoy a dinner with friends and family , get there around 430 before the dinner rush because it will get crowded on weekends.
Excellent food. Great service. Will definitely eat here again and again.
Simply excellent :)
Love the food. Great menu. Delicious vegetarian dishes.
Fresh ingredients...delightful wait staff
Great food and felt great eating rich and heart healthy meals
Friendly service, nice ambiance, and a menu with a lot of variety. Great for vegetarians.

Very good stir fry and gluten free!  My wife has celiac disease and they were very accommodating.  They use separate cutting boards and gloves when preparing the gluten free dishes.  There are plenty of options.  They also have a children's menu.  Not a large place, so you probably want to call for reservations, if you can.
Wonderful local food.  Very fresh
EXCELLENT for non-meat eaters!!  The food is amazingly flavorful.  I really enjoyed it.

Quirky, modern and delightfully different place with very fresh ingredients. Every meal here has been fantastic and the staff are amazing.  A few good rotating crafts are always available and their infused vodkas are a must try.
Went here for my first date and proposal nights with my wife.  Great atmosphere (very quiet and intimate) and the food is good.
Great healthy food that tastes delicious. My experience here was very relaxing. For my personal taste I wish it was decorated differently but it's a nice restaurant overall.
Place gets packed on the weekends. Service is decent and food is fresh. Menu is a little different though.

Their veggie salad is plentiful and healthy! It has romaine, hummus, avocado, cherry tomatoes, fried tofu, red cabbage and carrots. Their veggie stir fry comes in a multitude of ways depending on your flavor choice. Lovely relaxed atmosphere on a cute corner near shops!
I've had great experiences every single time I go. :-)
Always busy and always good. Service and food great.  Worth a visit or two or three!

A nice location for light/healthy, less-expensive fare on Market Street.  Good quality, healthy ingredients, but the portions are a little on the small size for the price (tho prices are reasonable for sit-down on Market). Coffee was good, the servers/service was friendly and attentive. There's a few outdoor seats available, and they have liquor license.
This is one of my favorite places, good food and drinks! Cant go wrong at the  orchard : )
Awesome food!!

The food is an extreme disappointment. My boyfriend and I have wasted our money here for the second and last time. We first went about a year ago, when I was served a bowl of bell pepper strips swimming in straight soy sauce. Yesterday, we made the mistake of dining here again. I order salmon and, for an upcharge of $6, was served tiny flecks of fish in a bowl of noodles. My boyfriend received a soggy sandwich.  Save your money and dine elsewhere.

Went with a friend from out of town and we were both impressed with the variety of healthy and tasty menu items. Service was great, food was flavorful, and I'll definitely go again. Lovely little place.
Wonderful salad and curried stir fry!  Great service.

I've been to the Orchard on several occasions the last year or so, and I find (IMO) it has some of the best tasting food in town. It doesn't taste mass-produced or processed. Many times I've left other restaurants feeling overly stuffed or just not great. Yet when I eat at the Orchard, I feel satisfied and that I ate a well balanced and healthy meal. The food is so fresh!  Service and staff each time I've been here have been great as well. If you want good quality ingredients and real whole foods that taste great, this is the place!
Have never been disappointed.  The menu is always fresh and seasonal, with interesting choices for any palate.  Even carnivores will walk away satisfied.
Alway great. Consistent and healthy.

As a resident of DT Frederick the Orchard stands out as one of my favorite restaurants.  Its as eclectic as all of downtown with a unique menu and staff.  Food is wholesome, natural and tasty.  Of particular high quality are all the soups and home made dressings offered.  Good choices for everyone including vegetarian.  Have to say the beer is always cold and dark beer selections are always good.

Incredibly tasty, incredibly healthy food, with plenty of vegetarian options, and great lunch prices. Salads and stir-fries shouldn't be this good. Fast, friendly, and professional service, too. I'm not a big fan of the decor—it's rather on the grandma side for my tastes—but everything else is perfect. (Your next best bet in a similar vein would be Acacia, about a block away.)

Hubby and I came in for dinner on Saturday night. This was the first time we've ever been to downtown Frederick for dinner. Parking was kind of a pain. We drove around for a good 20 minute looking for a spot, getting rejected from the closest parking garage--the "full" light clicked on right as we pressed the button for our ticket. We finally found another garage a couple blocks further and it only cost $1 to park which was a pleasant surprise.  Neither of us eat red meat or pork and it was really satisfying to go into a restaurant and have the option of ordering anything on the menu. We sat in the front room and it is pretty small, but once we were seated I was comfortable and my worry about being seated next to the bar was completely negated. The staffers are mostly of the tattooed hipster variety, but they were all friendly and helpful.  The Orchard has a pretty limited drink menu as well, but we each found libations which we enjoyed. I ordered a bowl of the tomato and basil bisque, which was awesome. The broccoli and potato soup was OK. Not as good as the bisque. I got the Jambalaya and I wasn't overly impressed with that either. I liked that it wasn't overly salty, but beyond that I found the flavors to be a little...bland. My husband got the Rockfish that was on special. He raved about it all night. Overall, dinner was good and I'm sure we'll be back.
